Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '32̣1'. Name Archembrotos. Same die is used in an example in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, and also there MGR P.16158. There are an unusually large number of dies used for this month.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (42)
